<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Start Here — Meet the Stock Analyzer agent</title>
<style>
  /* ---- tokens ---------------------------------------------------------- */
  :root{
    --cream:#FAF7F2; --paper:#FFFDF9; --ink:#2B2A28; --ink-soft:#55524C;
    --terra:#D97757; --teal:#4A9B8E; --wheat:#C79A2E; --slate:#5C84B1;
    --rule:#E4DED3; --rule-soft:#EFEAE0; --dim:#8A8880;
    --mono:"SF Mono",SFMono-Regular,Menlo,Consolas,"Liberation Mono",monospace;
    --sans:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){html{scroll-behavior:auto}}
  body{
    margin:0;background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink);
    font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;line-height:1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;
  }
  .wrap{max-width:1080px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px}

  /* ---- field-note gutter layout (signature) --------------------------- */
  .row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:150px 1fr;gap:32px;align-items:start}
  .note{
    font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--dim);
    text-align:right;padding-top:6px;border-right:1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-right:18px;position:sticky;top:24px;
  }
  .note b{color:var(--terra);font-weight:600;display:block;letter-spacing:.04em}
  @media (max-width:720px){
    .row{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:8px}
    .note{text-align:left;border-right:none;border-left:2px solid var(--terra);
      padding:2px 0 2px 12px;position:static}
  }

  /* ---- type ----------------------------------------------------------- */
  .eyebrow{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.18em;
    text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--terra);font-weight:600;margin:0 0 14px}
  h1{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;font-size:clamp(34px,6vw,58px);
    line-height:1.05;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin:0 0 18px}
  h2{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;font-size:26px;letter-spacing:-.01em;
    margin:0 0 16px;scroll-margin-top:24px}
  h3{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;font-size:17px;margin:0 0 6px}
  p{margin:0 0 16px;max-width:62ch}
  a{color:var(--terra);text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(217,119,87,.35)}
  a:hover{border-bottom-color:var(--terra)}
  code{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.88em;background:#F0EADF;
    padding:1px 6px;border-radius:4px;color:#6b4a38}
  kbd{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.82em;background:var(--ink);color:var(--cream);
    padding:3px 8px;border-radius:5px;box-shadow:0 2px 0 #000;font-weight:600}

  /* ---- hero ----------------------------------------------------------- */
  header.hero{padding:84px 0 56px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}
  .hero .lede{font-size:21px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:60ch}
  .stamp{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-family:var(--mono);
    font-size:12px;color:var(--dim);margin-top:30px;letter-spacing:.04em}
  .stamp .dot{width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--teal)}

  /* ---- the who/how split (signature) ---------------------------------- */
  section{padding:56px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}
  .split{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:8px}
  @media (max-width:720px){.split{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .card{background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:12px;
    padding:26px 26px 22px;position:relative}
  .card .tag{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.12em;
    text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600}
  .card.who{border-top:4px solid var(--terra)}
  .card.who .tag{color:var(--terra)}
  .card.how{border-top:4px solid var(--wheat)}
  .card.how .tag{color:var(--wheat)}
  .card h3{margin:10px 0 4px;font-size:20px}
  .card .sub{color:var(--dim);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px;margin-bottom:14px}
  .card p{font-size:15.5px;margin-bottom:0}
  .vs{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;color:var(--dim);text-align:center;
    margin:18px 0 4px;font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.2em}
  .keylines{margin:24px 0 4px;display:grid;gap:10px}
  .keyline{margin:0;max-width:none}
  .keynote{display:inline;color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:15px}
  .keyline mark{background:#FBE6A8;color:var(--ink);font-weight:700;
    padding:4px 10px;border-radius:4px;box-decoration-break:clone;
    -webkit-box-decoration-break:clone;line-height:1.9;font-size:17px}
  .vs-split{margin-top:14px}
  .vs-col{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.18em}
  .vs-col.who{color:var(--terra)}
  .vs-col.how{color:var(--wheat);text-align:right}
  @media (max-width:720px){.vs-col.how{text-align:left}}
  .exlist{list-style:none;padding:0;margin:14px 0 0;display:grid;gap:8px}
  .exlist li{font-size:14px;line-height:1.45;padding-left:16px;position:relative;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .exlist li::before{content:"›";position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--terra);font-family:var(--mono)}
  .card.how .exlist li::before{color:var(--wheat)}
  .exlist b{color:var(--ink);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13px}

  /* ---- figures -------------------------------------------------------- */
  figure{margin:0}
  .shot{width:100%;display:block;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid var(--rule);
    background:var(--paper);box-shadow:0 8px 30px rgba(43,42,40,.07)}
  figcaption{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px;color:var(--dim);
    margin-top:12px;line-height:1.5}
  figcaption b{color:var(--ink)}

  /* ---- step list ------------------------------------------------------ */
  .steps{counter-reset:s;list-style:none;padding:0;margin:8px 0 0}
  .steps>li{counter-increment:s;position:relative;padding:0 0 26px 56px;
    border-left:1px solid var(--rule);margin-left:18px}
  .steps>li:last-child{border-left-color:transparent;padding-bottom:0}
  .steps>li::before{content:counter(s,decimal-leading-zero);position:absolute;
    left:-18px;top:-4px;width:36px;height:36px;background:var(--paper);
    border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:50%;display:flex;
    align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:var(--mono);
    font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--terra)}
  .steps h3{margin-bottom:4px}
  .steps p{font-size:15.5px;margin-bottom:0}

  /* ---- anatomy of .claude (interactive) ------------------------------- */
  .anatomy{display:grid;grid-template-columns:230px 1fr;gap:0;margin-top:10px;
    border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;background:var(--paper)}
  @media (max-width:720px){.anatomy{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .tree{background:#F6F1E8;border-right:1px solid var(--rule);padding:14px 0}
  @media (max-width:720px){.tree{border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}}
  .tree button{display:block;width:100%;text-align:left;border:0;background:none;
    font-family:var(--mono);font-size:14px;color:var(--ink);padding:9px 18px;
    cursor:pointer;border-left:3px solid transparent}
  .tree button:hover{background:#EFE7D8}
  .tree button[aria-selected="true"]{background:var(--paper);border-left-color:var(--terra);
    color:var(--terra);font-weight:600}
  .tree .ico{display:inline-block;width:20px}
  .detail{padding:26px 28px}
  .detail h3{font-size:18px;margin-bottom:8px}
  .detail .path{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--dim);margin-bottom:14px}
  .detail p{font-size:15.5px;max-width:none}
  .detail .panel{display:none}
  .detail .panel.on{display:block;animation:fade .25s ease}
  @keyframes fade{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(4px)}to{opacity:1}}
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){.detail .panel.on{animation:none}}

  /* ---- skill chips ---------------------------------------------------- */
  .chips{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-top:6px}
  .chip{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px;background:#F3ECDD;color:#6b4a38;
    border:1px solid #E6D9BE;border-radius:20px;padding:5px 12px}
  button.chip{cursor:pointer;transition:background .12s,border-color .12s,transform .12s}
  button.chip:hover{background:#ECE0C8;transform:translateY(-1px)}
  button.chip.sel{background:var(--terra);color:#fff;border-color:var(--terra)}
  .skilldesc{margin-top:14px;background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left:3px solid var(--terra);border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;padding:14px 16px;
    font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--ink-soft);min-height:58px}
  .skilldesc b{color:var(--ink);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13.5px}
  .skilldesc .role{color:var(--terra);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px}
  .skilldesc .hint{color:var(--dim);font-style:italic}

  /* ---- callout / prereq ---------------------------------------------- */
  .callout{background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left:4px solid var(--teal);border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;
    padding:22px 26px;margin-top:8px}
  .callout.warn{border-left-color:var(--terra)}
  .callout h3{margin-bottom:6px}
  .callout p{margin-bottom:0;font-size:15.5px}

  /* ---- in/out folders ------------------------------------------------- */
  .io{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr auto 1fr;gap:18px;align-items:center;margin-top:8px}
  @media (max-width:720px){.io{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .io .box{background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:12px;padding:22px}
  .io .box.in{border-top:4px solid var(--slate)}
  .io .box.out{border-top:4px solid var(--teal)}
  .io .box .tag{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;
    text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600}
  .io .in .tag{color:var(--slate)} .io .out .tag{color:var(--teal)}
  .io .arrow{font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--dim);font-size:22px;text-align:center}
  @media (max-width:720px){.io .arrow{transform:rotate(90deg)}}
  .io code{display:inline-block;margin-top:4px}

  /* ---- deploy paths --------------------------------------------------- */
  .paths{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:16px;margin-top:8px}
  @media (max-width:720px){.paths{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .pathcard{display:block;background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius:12px;padding:20px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--ink);
    border-top:4px solid var(--rule);transition:border-color .15s,transform .15s}
  .pathcard:hover{border-top-color:var(--terra);transform:translateY(-2px)}
  .pathcard.here{border-top-color:var(--teal);background:#F4FAF8}
  .pathcard .ptag{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.12em;
    text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600;color:var(--dim)}
  .pathcard.here .ptag{color:var(--teal)}
  .pathcard h3{font-size:17px;margin:8px 0 8px}
  .pathcard p{font-size:14px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--ink-soft);margin:0 0 14px;max-width:none}
  .pathcard .plink{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11.5px;color:var(--terra);
    border-bottom:1px solid rgba(217,119,87,.35);padding-bottom:1px}
  footer{padding:48px 0 70px;color:var(--dim);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px}
  footer a{color:var(--dim)}
  .toc{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px;color:var(--dim);margin-top:18px;
    display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px 18px}
  .toc a{color:var(--ink-soft);border:0}
  .toc a:hover{color:var(--terra)}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">A field guide to one working agent</p>
    <h1>Meet the<br>Stock&nbsp;Analyzer.</h1>
    <p class="lede">You know how a research desk works. This folder turns that
      knowledge into a working Claude&nbsp;Code agent — and it's built to be
      <em>read</em>, not just run. Ten minutes here and the question
      <em>"what even is an agent?"</em> answers itself.</p>
    <div class="stamp"><span class="dot"></span> No code required to read along · macOS · open offline</div>
    <nav class="toc">
      <a href="#big-idea">The big idea</a>
      <a href="#need">What you need</a>
      <a href="#open">Open it</a>
      <a href="#reveal">Reveal .claude</a>
      <a href="#anatomy">Inside .claude</a>
      <a href="#run">Getting started</a>
      <a href="#io">Inputs &amp; outputs</a>
      <a href="#next">Make it yours</a>
      <a href="#deploy">Where it runs</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- ============================================================ BIG IDEA -->
<section id="big-idea">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <aside class="note"><b>start here</b>one sentence to hang everything else on</aside>
    <div>
      <h2>An agent is a who. A skill is a how.</h2>
      <p>That's the whole mental model, and it holds for <em>any</em> agent, in any
        domain. You give the agent a <b>goal</b>; it carries out <b>skills</b> —
        sets of instructions — to reach it.</p>
      <div class="split">
        <div class="card who">
          <span class="tag">The who · agent</span>
          <h3>A role, given an objective</h3>
          <p>Agents are <b>role-focused</b>. You hand one a <b>goal</b> — an
            objective, not step-by-step orders — and it decides <em>what to do
            next</em> to get there. They work best kept narrow: one clear domain,
            not a do-everything assistant.</p>
          <ul class="exlist">
            <li><b>A developer agent</b> → "ship the feature, keep tests green"</li>
            <li><b>A researcher agent</b> → "find what's worth a closer look today"</li>
            <li><b>A tester agent</b> → "break it before users do"</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card how">
          <span class="tag">The how · skill</span>
          <h3>A set of instructions</h3>
          <p>Skills are <b>sets of instructions</b> for one task — the recipe, the
            procedure, the steps and standards for doing a specific thing well.
            Each is small, self-contained, and reusable across agents.</p>
          <ul class="exlist">
            <li>The developer's: <b>run-migrations</b>, <b>open-a-PR</b></li>
            <li>The researcher's: <b>pull-filings</b>, <b>build-a-workbook</b></li>
            <li>The tester's: <b>write-fuzz-cases</b>, <b>diff-snapshots</b></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="split vs-split">
        <div class="vs-col who">↑ WHO DECIDES</div>
        <div class="vs-col how">HOW EXECUTES ↑</div>
      </div>
      <div class="keylines">
        <p class="keyline"><mark>Agents decide what skills they use to accomplish an objective.</mark></p>
        <p class="keyline"><mark>Skills instruct agents on how to properly leverage tools.</mark>
          <span class="keynote">— how to call an API, what to do with its response,
          which file format to write, when to stop.</span></p>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top:18px">The agent reads its own definition, then reaches
        for skills as the work calls for them. Skills generally don't know about
        each other, which is exactly why you can copy one into another agent or
        rewrite it without touching the rest.</p>

      <h3 style="margin:34px 0 4px;font-size:18px">In this folder, that's:</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:14px">The same idea, made concrete
        — one researcher agent and one of its eleven skills.</p>
      <div class="split">
        <div class="card who">
          <span class="tag">The who · agent</span>
          <h3>stock-analyzer</h3>
          <div class="sub">.claude/agents/stock-analyzer.md</div>
          <p>The role: "a desk-side research associate." Mostly plain prose — a job
            description you'd hand a new analyst.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card how">
          <span class="tag">The how · skill</span>
          <h3>growth-study</h3>
          <div class="sub">.claude/skills/growth-study/SKILL.md</div>
          <p>One ability: "spread the financials into a workbook." It does that one
            job well and is picked up when the moment calls for it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================================ NEED -->
<section id="need">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <aside class="note"><b>prerequisite</b>the one thing to install first</aside>
    <div>
      <h2>What you need: Claude Code</h2>
      <p>This whole folder runs inside <b>Claude&nbsp;Code</b>, Anthropic's
        command-line coding agent. It's the program that reads the agent
        definition and does the work. If you don't have it yet, start here:</p>
      <div class="callout">
        <h3>Install Claude Code first</h3>
        <p>Read the overview and follow the install steps at
          <a href="https://code.claude.com/docs/en/overview" target="_blank" rel="noopener">code.claude.com/docs/en/overview</a>.
          Once <code>claude</code> runs in your terminal, come back here.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================================ OPEN -->
<section id="open">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <aside class="note"><b>look first</b>get into the folder</aside>
    <div>
      <h2>Open the folder</h2>
      <p>In Finder, this folder (<code>market-researcher</code>) looks ordinary at
        first — a readme, a couple of launchers, the input/output trays. The
        interesting part is hidden.</p>
      <figure>
        <img class="shot" alt="Finder window showing the market-researcher folder with agent-inputs, agent-outputs, launchers, README and start-here.html. The .claude folder is hidden." src="__FINDER_HIDDEN__">
        <figcaption><b>The folder as you first see it.</b> Notice there's no
          <code>.claude</code> yet — macOS hides anything that starts with a dot.
          You'll launch the agent from here in a moment — first, a look at what's inside.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================================ REVEAL -->
<section id="reveal">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <aside class="note"><b>look first</b>see what's really in here</aside>
    <div>
      <h2>Reveal the hidden <code>.claude</code> folder</h2>
      <p>The agent and its skills live in a folder named <code>.claude</code>.
        The leading dot keeps it out of the way during normal use — but you want
        to see it. In any Finder window, press:</p>
      <p style="font-size:22px;margin:6px 0 22px">
        <kbd>⌘</kbd> &nbsp;<kbd>⇧</kbd> &nbsp;<kbd>.</kbd>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size:15px;color:var(--dim);font-family:var(--mono)">Command + Shift + Period</span>
      </p>
      <p>Hidden files fade into view. Press it again any time to hide them.</p>
      <figure style="margin-top:18px">
        <img class="shot" alt="The same Finder window after pressing Command Shift Period. Now .claude and .venv appear, dimmed, with .claude selected." src="__FINDER_SHOWN__">
        <figcaption><b>After the shortcut.</b> <code>.claude</code> and
          <code>.venv</code> appear (dimmed, because they're hidden by default).
          <code>.claude</code> is the one that matters — open it next.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================================ ANATOMY -->
<section id="anatomy">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <aside class="note"><b>look first</b>read the four things inside</aside>
    <div>
      <h2>Inside <code>.claude</code></h2>
      <p>Four things. Click each to see what it's for — this is the entire anatomy
        of the agent.</p>
      <figure style="margin:6px 0 26px">
        <img class="shot" alt="Finder window showing the contents of the .claude folder: agents, skills, plans folders and a settings.json file." src="__FINDER_CLAUDE__">
        <figcaption><b>The contents of <code>.claude</code>.</b> Three folders and one settings file.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div class="anatomy">
        <div class="tree" role="tablist" aria-label="Contents of .claude">
          <button role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-panel="agents"><span class="ico">📁</span>agents/</button>
          <button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-panel="skills"><span class="ico">📁</span>skills/</button>
          <button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-panel="plans"><span class="ico">📁</span>plans/</button>
          <button role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-panel="settings"><span class="ico">📄</span>settings.json</button>
        </div>
        <div class="detail">
          <div class="panel on" id="agents" role="tabpanel">
            <h3>agents/ — the role</h3>
            <div class="path">.claude/agents/&lt;name&gt;.md</div>
            <p>One Markdown file per agent. Here there's exactly one — the role this
              whole folder is built around:</p>
            <div class="chips">
              <button class="chip sel" data-agent="stock-analyzer">📄 stock-analyzer.md</button>
            </div>
            <div class="skilldesc">
              <b>stock-analyzer.md</b> <span class="role">— the agent definition</span><br>
              The file that <em>is</em> the agent: who it is, the workflow it follows, the
              guardrails it won't cross, and the skills it can call. Read it like an
              analyst's job description. The first two lines — <code>name</code> and
              <code>description</code> — are all Claude needs to know when to use it;
              everything below is the playbook.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="panel" id="skills" role="tabpanel">
            <h3>skills/ — the recipes</h3>
            <div class="path">.claude/skills/&lt;name&gt;/SKILL.md</div>
            <p>One folder per skill, each a self-contained recipe the agent follows.
              Every <code>SKILL.md</code> has the same shape: a description, the output
              it owns, numbered steps, the standards that make it trustworthy, and the
              mistakes to avoid. <b>Click a skill</b> to see what it does:</p>
            <div class="chips" id="skillchips">
              <button class="chip" data-skill="ensure-deps">ensure-deps</button><button class="chip" data-skill="ticker-discovery">ticker-discovery</button><button class="chip" data-skill="stock-discovery">stock-discovery</button><button class="chip" data-skill="hidden-opportunities">hidden-opportunities</button><button class="chip" data-skill="ticker-data">ticker-data</button><button class="chip" data-skill="stock-analysis">stock-analysis</button><button class="chip" data-skill="growth-study">growth-study</button><button class="chip" data-skill="xlsx-author">xlsx-author</button><button class="chip" data-skill="thesis-stress-test">thesis-stress-test</button><button class="chip" data-skill="explain-agent">explain-agent</button><button class="chip" data-skill="onboarding-guide">onboarding-guide</button>
            </div>
            <div class="skilldesc" id="skilldesc" aria-live="polite">
              <span class="hint">↑ Pick a skill to read its one-line job.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="panel" id="plans" role="tabpanel">
            <h3>plans/ — how it got built</h3>
            <div class="path">.claude/plans/</div>
            <p>Notes-to-self the agent wrote while planning bigger changes — here,
              the refactor that turned this into the Stock Analyzer. Not required to
              run anything; it's the paper trail, useful when you want to understand
              <em>why</em> the folder looks the way it does.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="panel" id="settings" role="tabpanel">
            <h3>settings.json — the permissions</h3>
            <div class="path">.claude/settings.json</div>
            <p>The rules of engagement: which commands and web domains the agent may
              touch (<code>allow</code>) and which it must never (<code>deny</code> —
              e.g. reading <code>.env</code> secrets or deleting files). This is how
              you keep an autonomous agent on a short, explicit leash.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============================================================ GETTING STARTED -->
<section id="run">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <aside class="note"><b>getting started</b>four steps, start to finish</aside>
    <div>
      <h2>Getting started</h2>
      <p>You've seen what's in the folder. Now run it — four steps.</p>

      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <h3>Open a Claude Code session in this folder</h3>
          <p>Double-click <code>Open in Claude.command</code> — it launches Claude Code
            already pointed here. (First time, you may need to right-click → Open so
            macOS trusts it.) Or open a terminal in this folder and type
            <code>claude</code>. Either way you land in a session.</p>
          <figure style="margin:14px 0 4px">
            <img class="shot" alt="Finder window with the file 'Open in Claude.command' selected, labeled double-click this." src="__FINDER_LAUNCH__">
            <figcaption><b>The file to double-click.</b> It's the terminal-badge
              <code>.command</code> file — it opens a session in this folder for you.</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Wait for Claude to start</h3>
          <p>A terminal window opens and Claude Code boots up. When it's ready you'll
            see the welcome splash and an empty input box with a <code>›</code> prompt —
            that's Claude waiting for your first message.</p>
          <figure style="margin:14px 0 4px">
            <img class="shot" alt="The Claude Code startup splash: a pixel mascot, 'Claude Code v2.1.183', 'Opus 4.8 with high effort', the working directory, and an empty input box with a cursor, waiting for input." src="__CLAUDE_SPLASH__">
            <figcaption><b>Claude is ready.</b> The empty <code>›</code> box means it's
