          </figure>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Type <code>/agents</code> to confirm the agent is there</h3>
          <p>Claude Code reads the <code>.claude/agents/</code> folder automatically.
            Type <code>/agents</code> and you'll see <code>stock-analyzer</code> listed
            as a <b>Project agent</b> — already configured, nothing to install.</p>
          <figure style="margin:14px 0 4px">
            <img class="shot" alt="The Claude Code /agents Library panel showing stock-analyzer registered as a Project agent loaded from .claude/agents, with model set to inherit." src="__CLAUDE_AGENTS__">
            <figcaption><b><code>/agents</code> → Library.</b> Picked up from
